  "description": {
    "en": {
      "provenance": "imported",
      "value": "Health & Nutrition The objective of the project is to provide safe and regular crossing for migrants amid COVID-19 by improved capacity of isolation centers and ground crossing points.PLANNED INTERVENTION:Outcome 1: Health-based facilities at six isolation centers and six GCPs are strengthened.This outcome will strengthen the overall capacity of the health-based facilities through provision of crucial equipment and human resources. The safety of migrants and personnel at GCPs and isolation centers will be ensured through provision of safety gears and medical equipment, provision of semi-permanent health desks to support health screening and testing to meet anticipated high influx of return migrants and supporting the provincial governments in developing contingency plans for public health emergencies. Personnel will be trained on the use of safety gears; medical equipment will be provided. The project will support through provision of technical equipment including tablets and computers as well as solar panels at targeted isolation centers and GCPs to strengthen reporting and recording mechanisms, COVID19 screening and referrals, and logistical management"
    },
    "ne": null
  },
